source.inline: if application "Google Chrome" is running then	tell application "Google Chrome"		repeat with t in tabs of windows			tell t				if URL starts with "https://music.youtube.com" or URL starts with "http://music.youtube.com" then					try						local groupName, trackName, timeTrack, response						set response to ""						set groupName to  execute JavaScript "document.getElementsByClassName('byline ytmusic-player-bar')[0]?.firstChild.innerText || ''"						set trackName to  execute JavaScript "document.getElementsByClassName('title ytmusic-player-bar')[0]?.innerText|| ''"												if groupName is not equal to "" then							set response to response & groupName						end if												if trackName is not equal to "" then							if response is not equal to "" then								set response to response & " - " & trackName							else								set response to response & trackName							end if						end if												if response is equal to "" then return "..........................."						return response					on error errorMsg						return errorMsg					end try				end if			end tell		end repeat	end tellend ifreturn "Open YouTube Music"

actionAppleScript.inline: if application "Google Chrome" is not running then	tell application "Google Chrome" to activateend iftell application "Google Chrome"	repeat with t in tabs of windows		tell t			if URL starts with "https://music.youtube.com" or URL starts with "http://music.youtube.com" then				return			end if		end tell	end repeatend telltell application "Google Chrome" to open location "https://music.youtube.com"

source.inline: set cpu to do shell script "ps axo %cpu | awk '{s+=$1}END{print s}'"return cpu & "%"

actionAppleScript.inline: activate application "Activity Monitor"tell application "System Events"	tell process "Activity Monitor"		tell radio button "CPU" of radio group 1 of group 2 of toolbar 1 of window 1 to perform action "AXPress"	end tellend tell

source.inline: set mem to do shell script "ps -A -o %mem | awk '{s+=$1}END{print s}'"return mem & "%"

actionAppleScript.inline: activate application "Activity Monitor"tell application "System Events"	tell process "Activity Monitor"		tell radio button "CPU" of radio group 1 of group 2 of toolbar 1 of window 1 to perform action "AXPress"	end tellend tell
